cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV. 

This paper is about creating a benchmark dataset for Machine Translation of Noisy Text (MTNT), which is a problem in natural language processing. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models for handling noisy text, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of adaptation on a small training set, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the dataset includes comments on Reddit, which could involve computer vision techniques for processing images and videos, making cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) a possible sub-category as well.
